description.narrative: UNICEF programmes are provided with technical assistance, procurement and logistics support, which contributes to Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The identity, direction and well-being of UNICEF and staff are managed efficiently and effectively to enable the achievement of results for children in the country

title.narrative: UNICEF programmes are provided with technical assistance, procurement and logistics support

description.narrative: The annual supply and logistics services plan was prepared early in the year, with a focus on the ongoing COVID-19 response but was significantly altered following the military takeover. Due to significant changes in the operating context, all programmes transitioned into emergency response, and the Supply Logistics Unit refocused its activities accordingly. Numerous aspects of; procurement and logistics processes were simplified following the declaration of the L2 Corporate Emergency Response for Myanmar from 1 July 2021 . Despite the context-related challeges, the supply and logistics operations remained effective and efficient during the year, supporting achievements of the changed programmatic interventions.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:08/01/2022
